WEBVTT

00:08.375 --> 00:10.166
[man 1] We the People.

00:10.833 --> 00:12.416
[man 2] We the People.

00:12.500 --> 00:13.625
[man 3] We the People.

00:13.708 --> 00:16.083
-[man 4] We the People.
-[man 5] We the People.

00:16.166 --> 00:18.708
-[man 6] We the People!
-[man 7] We the People!

00:18.791 --> 00:21.500
-[man 8] We the People!
-[man 9] We the People!

00:21.583 --> 00:22.458
[shushes]

00:22.541 --> 00:25.166
Wait… [breathes deeply]

00:25.250 --> 00:26.708
We the People…

00:29.166 --> 00:30.375
-[all cheering]
-Yeah!

00:30.458 --> 00:33.583
-We the People!
-We the People!

00:33.666 --> 00:35.916
Sorry, Tom, "We the People" it is.

00:36.000 --> 00:38.791
You can use "Us rich white guys"
on your Christmas card.

00:38.875 --> 00:41.791
Mmm, at Dartmouth,
we play with actual paddles.

00:41.875 --> 00:44.708
Nobody fucking cares
how you do it at Dartmouth, Tom.

00:44.791 --> 00:45.666
[all laughing]

00:45.750 --> 00:48.500
Franklin, these bucktooth
fun police can suck it

00:48.583 --> 00:50.583
because we've done it, boys!

00:50.666 --> 00:54.250
-We have declared our independence!
-[all] Huzzah!

00:54.333 --> 00:58.250
Lincoln and his idiot lackey, Washington,
are gonna be pissed they missed this.

00:58.333 --> 01:00.458
-[chuckles]
-Ooh! We should take a picture!

01:00.541 --> 01:02.083
Say "cheese."

01:02.166 --> 01:03.250
Benedict Arnold?

01:03.916 --> 01:06.750
-It's the Redcoats! Run!
-[men yelling]

01:06.833 --> 01:08.458
[screaming]

01:12.708 --> 01:13.833
What is happ--

01:14.916 --> 01:15.791
[yells]

01:18.041 --> 01:21.416
-[head] No, no, no!
-Declarate this!

01:34.458 --> 01:35.291
[screeches]

01:42.041 --> 01:45.250
Now I just have to catch a show
with my old chum,

01:45.333 --> 01:47.875
Abraham Lincoln.

01:50.500 --> 01:53.416
[Abe] Four score and seven years ago,

01:53.500 --> 01:56.875
I swore an oath to never tell a lie.

01:56.958 --> 02:02.125
To be true to my family, my friends,
and the Republic for which they stand,

02:02.208 --> 02:07.708
which is why I am compelled,
by divine duty, to tell you

02:07.791 --> 02:10.583
your prices are fucking insane!

02:10.666 --> 02:13.125
Wow, easy. Take it up with the King.

02:13.208 --> 02:15.625
-Something about taxation!
-[colonists] Yeah, that's right!

02:15.708 --> 02:17.750
Dude, I just work here.

02:17.833 --> 02:20.208
But… Uh…
Something about representation!

02:20.291 --> 02:21.958
-Yeah!
-You tell 'em, Abe!

02:22.041 --> 02:24.833
-[George] Abe!
-This isn't over, pal!

02:24.916 --> 02:25.791
[colonists] Yeah!

02:25.875 --> 02:28.541
[sighs] You don't gotta be
such a damn tyrant about it.

02:28.625 --> 02:31.250
[George] Abe! Look at me! [laughs]

02:31.333 --> 02:33.916
-This guy dared me to climb up here.
-[man] No, I didn't.

02:34.000 --> 02:36.208
Well, you should've! Whoo!

02:36.875 --> 02:37.958
-[colonists cheering]
-Yeah!

02:38.041 --> 02:40.875
George, you are a wild man.

02:40.958 --> 02:42.500
[sighs] What can I say?

02:42.583 --> 02:45.250
Somebody's gotta
balance out all your boring politics.

02:45.333 --> 02:48.666
[chuckles] George, I guess
that's what makes us such a good team.

02:48.750 --> 02:53.250
A team that will last until we both die
of natural causes and old age,

02:53.333 --> 02:54.333
in our forties.

02:54.416 --> 02:57.541
But I do wish ya cared
about more than just partying.

02:57.625 --> 03:00.625
[gasps] Abe! I care
about more than that, all right?

03:00.708 --> 03:04.000
I also care about… how good we look!

03:04.083 --> 03:07.958
Oh, George.
You paid 35 bucks for a T-blouse?

03:08.041 --> 03:12.416
No, I paid 70 bucks for two T-blouses.

03:12.500 --> 03:13.333
Twinsies!

03:13.416 --> 03:17.083
George, I wish I had
a million friends like you.

03:17.166 --> 03:19.916
-Should I put it on my body?
-Yeah, put it on your body.

03:20.000 --> 03:23.208
Oh, it feels so soft on my body.

03:23.291 --> 03:25.958
-It's like a blend. Is it a blend?
-It's a tri-blend.

03:26.041 --> 03:28.791
Oh, it's so soft,
I'd swear it's a quad blend.

03:28.875 --> 03:31.125
-I know. [sighs]
-Oh, shit, oh!

03:31.208 --> 03:32.166
Oh, here comes Ben.

03:32.250 --> 03:35.000
-Ooh! Uh, hey, Ben.
-Benedict.

03:35.083 --> 03:38.333
Oh, sorry. Last two.

03:39.583 --> 03:40.583
[drums beating]

03:45.416 --> 03:47.000
[crowd cheering]

03:51.333 --> 03:53.333
I'm so glad you came.

03:53.416 --> 03:56.833
Mmm, I was worried
that you might have caught wind

03:56.916 --> 03:58.250
of my little surprise.

03:58.333 --> 03:59.416
No, not at all, man.

03:59.500 --> 04:02.500
These are boffo seats!
We didn't even see this coming at all.

04:02.583 --> 04:03.958
What are you up to?

04:04.041 --> 04:06.541
You hate surprises and general whimsy.

04:06.625 --> 04:08.583
I've always told you, Abraham,

04:08.666 --> 04:10.958
that your revolution
would be the end of you.

04:11.041 --> 04:14.500
And I've always told you, Ben,
that I was willing to take that chance.

04:14.583 --> 04:17.333
That we should all
be willing to take that chance.

04:17.416 --> 04:19.625
[laughs]

04:19.708 --> 04:21.708
Yes, you have.

04:21.791 --> 04:24.541
The only problem is
you assumed, all this time,

04:24.625 --> 04:27.958
that I'm part of your "we," when, in fact,

04:28.041 --> 04:31.416
I'm with a different "we," now.

04:32.916 --> 04:35.125
Uh, I didn't… I don't get it.

04:35.208 --> 04:38.041
I changed teams, assholes.

04:38.125 --> 04:40.208
Oh, Ben, good for you!

04:40.291 --> 04:43.125
I'm so glad
that you're embracing your true self.

04:43.208 --> 04:45.666
No! I'm gonna be fuckin' rich.

04:45.750 --> 04:49.541
Oh, Rich sounds like a great guy,
would love to meet him.

04:49.625 --> 04:52.125
-We could do a double date?
-You're misunderstanding.

04:52.208 --> 04:54.125
-I'll be doing the Redcoat Shuffle.
-Hey.

04:54.208 --> 04:57.000
Whatever you guys do
in private is your business.

04:57.083 --> 04:58.916
That's one of the things
we're fighting for!

04:59.000 --> 05:01.125
Stop being so damn accepting for a minute!

05:01.208 --> 05:04.541
I have aligned myself with the Brits.

05:04.625 --> 05:06.291
Oh. Ohh!

05:06.375 --> 05:08.083
[hesitating] George, are you hearing this?

05:08.166 --> 05:09.583
Are you seeing this?

05:09.666 --> 05:12.916
Abe, they're using things as instruments
that you're not supposed to use.

05:13.000 --> 05:15.208
-It's crazy!
-George, fuck!

05:15.291 --> 05:17.791
[hesitates] You've sided
with the fun police?

05:17.875 --> 05:20.833
Something about taxation.
Don't you remember?

05:20.916 --> 05:24.458
Hot take, Abe. Fun sucks.

05:24.541 --> 05:27.333
The Declaration was signed tonight, Ben.

05:27.416 --> 05:30.416
You're too late
to stop the revolution. Ha-ha!

05:30.500 --> 05:32.416
-Oh, am I?
-[Abe gasps]

05:32.500 --> 05:35.791
-Your friends in revolution are all dead.
-[Abe] What?

05:35.875 --> 05:38.791
And as for your precious
Declaration of Independence…

05:38.875 --> 05:41.833
-Oh, it's beautiful!
-A-Kelly Ripa!

05:41.916 --> 05:43.333
[Abe] No!

05:43.416 --> 05:45.500
But you're Benedict "Cosby" Arnold!

05:45.583 --> 05:47.916
-You're better than this!
-You're right.

05:48.000 --> 05:49.541
I am.

05:50.291 --> 05:51.708
[growls]

05:53.625 --> 05:54.875
[screams]

05:55.916 --> 05:56.791
[groans]

05:56.875 --> 06:00.041
Abe, what the… Oh, my God.
Your neck's… Oh, my God!

06:00.125 --> 06:02.916
Your neck is bleeding!
Is this part of the show?

06:03.000 --> 06:05.125
Look, I don't do well
with interactive theater, okay?

06:05.208 --> 06:06.500
It kinda freaks me out.

06:06.583 --> 06:08.750
I know. That's great.
We're number one, I get that.

06:08.833 --> 06:10.875
But I don't see what that has to do with…

06:10.958 --> 06:12.583
Arnold, behind you.

06:12.666 --> 06:14.500
No, Abe, I'm George.

06:14.583 --> 06:16.125
It's George!

06:16.208 --> 06:18.291
George, turn around.

06:18.375 --> 06:20.083
Ben! Ben, what the fuck, man?

06:20.166 --> 06:21.875
[slurps]

06:21.958 --> 06:25.000
Someday, Georgie,
you'll have to draft a document

06:25.083 --> 06:28.708
that specifically outlines
the punishment for what I just did.

06:28.791 --> 06:32.000
But for now, I bid you adieu.

06:32.541 --> 06:33.750
Nyah!

06:34.666 --> 06:36.250
[grunts]

06:36.333 --> 06:39.333
Sic semper my dick, bitches!

06:39.916 --> 06:41.083
[crowd cheers]

06:41.166 --> 06:42.625
This is the weirdest show.

06:42.708 --> 06:44.000
Abe. [spits]

06:44.125 --> 06:45.375
Abe, are you okay?

06:45.458 --> 06:48.875
-No, my throat has been roadhoused.
-[spitting] Ah, it's in my mouth.

06:48.958 --> 06:50.583
I'm dying, George.

06:50.666 --> 06:53.458
No, you will not die!
You shut your mouth!

06:53.541 --> 06:56.166
-I will shut my mouth.
-[spitting]

06:56.250 --> 06:58.416
-Forever.
-Stop it! [spits]

06:58.500 --> 07:02.416
-Abe, you're gonna make it.
-Yes, to the other side.

07:02.500 --> 07:05.125
No! Back to this side! Where you belong!

07:05.208 --> 07:08.958
George, you must free the colonies.

07:09.041 --> 07:13.041
No! That's your thing, Abe.
It's not mine.

07:13.125 --> 07:16.666
It's yours now, George.
I believe in you.

07:16.750 --> 07:19.208
-[spits]
-Free the colonies.

07:19.291 --> 07:21.375
Found a new country.

07:21.458 --> 07:22.958
Name her…

07:23.041 --> 07:26.541
Name her what, babe?
You tell me what you want me to name her.

07:26.625 --> 07:28.875
God damn it! You son of a bitch!

07:28.958 --> 07:33.625
Whatever you tell me to name her,
that's what I'm gonna name her, Abie!

07:33.708 --> 07:37.541
Name her America.

07:37.625 --> 07:38.958
[eagle screeches]

07:40.250 --> 07:41.666
Is that your top choice?

07:41.750 --> 07:43.875
We can spitball some options,
see if we can beat it.

07:43.958 --> 07:45.875
There is no time, George.

07:45.958 --> 07:48.000
My death-shit is imminent.

07:48.083 --> 07:50.541
America, okay? Just remember…

07:50.625 --> 07:54.166
-[groans and farts] America.
-[eagle screeches]

07:55.250 --> 07:56.958
[farts]

07:58.250 --> 07:59.375
A-- [gags]

07:59.458 --> 08:00.833
Nope. [retches]

08:00.916 --> 08:03.000
A-- [retches, coughs]

08:03.083 --> 08:04.291
Okay, hold it.

08:04.375 --> 08:06.958
Abe!

08:07.916 --> 08:09.083
Stand ready.

08:09.166 --> 08:12.791
A vengeful Washington
will be here in three, two…

08:14.000 --> 08:15.375
Hey, dickhole!

08:15.458 --> 08:17.208
It's time to… Oh, fuck me.

08:17.291 --> 08:19.375
Yes. Fuck you, indeed.

08:23.375 --> 08:24.250
Subdue him.

08:24.333 --> 08:26.916
I wish to shame him
with a cutting dialogue.

08:27.666 --> 08:29.541
-[cracks neck]
-Hello, guv.

08:29.625 --> 08:31.458
[battle cries]

08:31.541 --> 08:34.250
[Benedict] I know betrayal hurts, Georgie,

08:34.333 --> 08:39.583
and it can often rile in a man
motivation he didn't even know he had.

08:39.666 --> 08:40.708
But face facts.

08:40.791 --> 08:43.541
With Abe and the rest of your
revolutionaries gone,

08:43.625 --> 08:46.083
on account of me having
killed them all just now,

08:46.166 --> 08:50.208
your tired, party-boy antics
are bound to fail.

08:50.291 --> 08:52.666
You'll never be the leader Abe was.

08:52.750 --> 08:53.666
[grunts]

08:53.750 --> 08:57.250
Because you lack Abe's brains, his heart,

08:57.333 --> 09:02.041
and, most importantly, his soul.

09:02.125 --> 09:05.416
Without him, the revolution is dead.

09:06.125 --> 09:09.083
[yells] Rah!

09:11.000 --> 09:12.083
-Whoo!
-[motor roars]

09:12.166 --> 09:15.375
That cherry tree
didn't chop its fucking self down!

09:15.458 --> 09:16.333
Let's go!

09:21.125 --> 09:24.500
Ah, are you a miniboss, or what?
Do something!

09:31.000 --> 09:32.375
[screeches]

09:35.791 --> 09:37.083
[clanking]

09:37.166 --> 09:38.250
[grunts]

09:41.375 --> 09:42.208
[grunts]

09:47.208 --> 09:48.500
Jesus Christ!

09:48.583 --> 09:50.750
Transporter, go!

09:50.833 --> 09:52.458
Let's get you transported.

09:52.541 --> 09:54.875
[engine whirs]

09:58.791 --> 10:00.625
[grunts]

10:00.708 --> 10:04.333
I can't believe we ever let you
into the Three Fuckateers!

10:04.416 --> 10:07.125
I'm changing our Netflix password!

10:07.208 --> 10:08.625
Transporter, the bridge!

10:10.666 --> 10:11.625
[thuds]

10:11.708 --> 10:13.416
[grunts]

10:16.583 --> 10:19.125
Ah! [groans]

10:19.791 --> 10:21.208
Fuckin' bridges.

10:21.291 --> 10:22.666
Ah, Christ.

10:22.750 --> 10:23.666
[Benedict chuckles]

10:23.750 --> 10:24.583
[George] What now?

10:25.333 --> 10:28.750
Oh, Georgie, I almost forgot.

10:28.833 --> 10:30.625
I have something from your king.

10:31.208 --> 10:33.625
This is for you.

10:33.708 --> 10:35.875
["Rule Brittania!" playing]

10:35.958 --> 10:37.416
[laughing]

10:39.125 --> 10:40.916
"This is for you."
[continues laughing]

10:41.000 --> 10:42.333
I'm so clever!

10:45.125 --> 10:46.291
[George] No.

10:47.083 --> 10:49.250
This is for…

10:50.083 --> 10:53.750
America!

10:56.958 --> 10:57.833
[window opens]

10:57.916 --> 11:00.541
[man] Shut the fuck up!

11:00.625 --> 11:03.458
-[smacks lips] Yep.
-[dog barks distantly]

11:03.541 --> 11:04.416
All right.

11:16.458 --> 11:18.000
[Martha singing] ♪ Close your eyes ♪

11:18.083 --> 11:19.166
[strumming guitar]

11:19.250 --> 11:22.750
♪ Give me your hand, darling ♪

11:23.333 --> 11:26.583
♪ Do you feel my heart beating? ♪

11:27.250 --> 11:29.833
♪ Do you understand? ♪

11:29.916 --> 11:33.250
♪ Do you feel the same? ♪

11:34.083 --> 11:38.708
♪ Am I only dreaming? ♪

11:39.458 --> 11:42.333
♪ Is this burnin' ♪

11:42.916 --> 11:43.875
[sobbing]

11:43.958 --> 11:46.958
♪ An eternal flame? ♪

11:47.041 --> 11:48.791
[humming]

11:54.958 --> 11:56.000
[music stops]

11:56.083 --> 11:56.916
[birds chirping]

11:57.000 --> 11:57.958
He sewed it by hand

11:58.041 --> 12:00.875
when Trishelle came down
with dengue fever last May Day.

12:00.958 --> 12:03.791
He laid it upon her and she healed.

12:03.875 --> 12:05.708
And now, she lays it upon him,

12:06.291 --> 12:07.791
but he will never heal.

12:08.500 --> 12:09.500
John 3:16.

12:11.083 --> 12:12.250
[strums electric guitar]

12:12.333 --> 12:14.916
A gift from Mozart himself.

12:16.666 --> 12:21.666
Silenced now, like its owner, forever.

12:24.875 --> 12:25.875
[guitar stops playing]

12:25.958 --> 12:28.333
You're, uh--
[clears throat] Martha Dandridge.

12:28.416 --> 12:30.125
You were there that night, on stage.

12:30.208 --> 12:33.916
And you are George Washington,
inventor of peanut butter.

12:34.000 --> 12:35.000
The same.

12:35.083 --> 12:37.291
Abraham Lincoln's best friend.

12:37.375 --> 12:38.250
[whispers] Forever.

12:38.333 --> 12:40.833
You've suffered a tremendous loss.

12:41.541 --> 12:43.583
You should not be alone tonight.

12:43.666 --> 12:44.666
-Oh!
-Ahh!

12:44.750 --> 12:46.500
-Yes! Yes!
-Ah!

12:46.583 --> 12:48.958
-[shrieks]
-[grunts]

12:49.041 --> 12:53.500
-[George shouting]
-[Martha shrieking]

12:53.583 --> 12:56.666
-Uh…
-What is it? You can tell me, Martha.

12:56.750 --> 12:59.041
-You can tell me anything.
-Well… [breathing heavily]

13:00.125 --> 13:02.333
-I'm pregnant.
-What? Just now?

13:02.416 --> 13:03.625
-Yeah.
-You're sure?

13:03.708 --> 13:05.958
-A woman knows.
-[laughs]

13:06.041 --> 13:07.833
A miracle has befallen us!

13:07.916 --> 13:10.083
-Has it?
-It has! Yes.

13:10.166 --> 13:11.666
Oh, but has it?

13:11.750 --> 13:13.041
All I've ever wanted, Martha,

13:13.125 --> 13:15.708
was the one thing
I never had, a loving family.

13:15.791 --> 13:17.583
-Gross, you were an orphan?
-What?

13:17.666 --> 13:19.750
-Of course not! God, no. Ew.
-Ugh! Phew!

13:19.833 --> 13:22.375
No, but look,
my father was a real man's man,

13:22.458 --> 13:24.291
which is to say, like all men's men,

13:24.375 --> 13:27.625
he disrespected my mother
and punished me for his insecurities.

13:27.708 --> 13:31.708
And see, this will be a great opportunity
to break that cycle, if you will.

13:32.250 --> 13:35.375
You know, there can be
no spring without winter. John 3:16.

13:35.458 --> 13:37.166
That's beautiful, George.

13:37.250 --> 13:38.250
Oh, hey, what's this?

13:38.333 --> 13:40.125
Oh. [chuckles]

13:40.208 --> 13:43.833
Just [sighs] a box
of misty water-colored memories.

13:43.916 --> 13:47.208
[chuckles] Oh, look, the day we first met.

13:47.291 --> 13:49.375
I was hiding from my father in the woods,

13:49.458 --> 13:51.791
and he had been drinking
and listening to Kid Rock again.

13:51.875 --> 13:54.916
And then, I encountered a boy,
no older than me,

13:55.000 --> 13:58.375
and he smelled of possums and night soil.

13:58.458 --> 14:02.250
We couldn't have been any more different.
And yet, he opened up his arms to me

14:02.333 --> 14:04.333
and he took me up into his tree home.

14:04.416 --> 14:07.708
It was the first time
that I understood what family was.

14:07.791 --> 14:10.166
Aw… #Blessed.

14:10.250 --> 14:13.000
[George chuckles]
This is his seventh birthday.

14:13.083 --> 14:16.125
I had to get him a hat to cover
that hideous, malformed head of his.

14:16.208 --> 14:19.166
Who could have known
that it would come to be his trademark?

14:19.250 --> 14:21.250
Oh, prom! Wow!

14:21.333 --> 14:23.375
We lost our virginities
that night. [chuckles]

14:24.000 --> 14:25.375
-Together.
-Oh, I get it.

14:25.458 --> 14:26.458
I've been to Paris.

14:26.541 --> 14:28.500
Oh, man, we had so many plans.

14:28.583 --> 14:31.333
Oh, Sky Camp! Junior Templar Scouts.

14:31.416 --> 14:33.791
[gasps] Our semi-pro
rolling-circle-with-a-stick team.

14:34.375 --> 14:35.833
What is this even… [chuckles]

14:35.916 --> 14:36.916
-[grunts]
-Oh!

14:37.000 --> 14:37.875
-Oh!
-[gasps]

14:37.958 --> 14:41.208
-The famed "Lincoln Log!" [laughs]
-[chuckles] Yes!

14:41.291 --> 14:43.416
Abe, [laughs] you rapscallion.

14:43.500 --> 14:45.875
Oh. [sobbing]

14:45.958 --> 14:47.333
You rapscallion. [sobbing]

14:47.416 --> 14:48.375
Oh…

14:49.625 --> 14:50.875
George.

14:50.958 --> 14:53.166
-Oh, George. George!
-[George] What?

14:53.250 --> 14:54.916
-What?
-You know what you must do.

14:55.000 --> 14:58.166
Have a bunch more sex with you
until I start feeling better?

14:58.250 --> 15:01.333
-That'll work in the short term.
-[sobs] Okay, that's a great idea.

15:01.416 --> 15:04.166
No, no… No! George.

15:04.250 --> 15:06.125
You must avenge Abe.

15:06.208 --> 15:07.958
See his dream through.

