like, the nice part of town.

29:47.625 --> 29:51.125
Well, it smells like shit,
which reminds me,

29:51.208 --> 29:53.541
I need to make room for second breakfast.

29:53.625 --> 29:56.833
I've had my fill
of mushy peas and blood sausage.

29:56.916 --> 29:59.458
[Benedict] Yes, accommodations
at the top of your obelisk

29:59.541 --> 30:01.000
are more well-suited, my king.

30:01.083 --> 30:05.833
Then, I can assume everything
is proceeding as I have foreseen.

30:05.916 --> 30:07.875
Yes, your plan is proceeding.

30:07.958 --> 30:09.333
But we have had trouble

30:09.416 --> 30:12.166
with a certain colonist
not falling in line.

30:12.250 --> 30:14.416
Well, has he read the rules?

30:15.125 --> 30:19.416
The rules should always
be posted clearly in a public place

30:19.500 --> 30:21.875
where everyone can read them.

30:21.958 --> 30:24.500
Oh, can he… can he not read?

30:24.583 --> 30:27.583
Well, no, he has read them, Your Highness.

30:27.666 --> 30:30.666
However, he has chosen not to follow them.

30:30.750 --> 30:34.041
-[sputtering] But they are the rules!
-I know!

30:34.125 --> 30:38.875
What is the point of being a ruler
if people are not following your rules?

30:38.958 --> 30:41.083
This is, like, King Shit 101!

30:41.166 --> 30:43.041
I understand, my king.

30:43.125 --> 30:44.291
Not following the…

30:44.375 --> 30:47.625
[voice trembling] Arnold,
why, do you know what this is?

30:47.708 --> 30:50.666
-I do.
-It's rebellion!

30:50.750 --> 30:51.708
By definition.

30:51.791 --> 30:55.500
We cannot allow anything
to stop my plan, Arnold!

30:55.583 --> 30:58.250
Crush this illiterate rebel scum!

30:58.333 --> 31:00.416
It will be my pleasure.

31:01.125 --> 31:02.625
Excellent.

31:04.583 --> 31:07.416
[Samuel] Dudes, are we close yet?
I'm getting hangry.

31:07.500 --> 31:08.583
I could definitely eat.

31:08.666 --> 31:11.375
Oh, I saw a Boston Wild Wings
about a mile back.

31:11.458 --> 31:12.583
What's a mile?

31:12.666 --> 31:15.083
And I could totally
crush some B-dubs right now.

31:15.166 --> 31:17.416
Hey, hey! Knock it off, guys.

31:17.500 --> 31:19.583
First, we start a revolution.

31:19.666 --> 31:21.750
Then we can have
all the Boston Wild Wings

31:21.833 --> 31:23.041
that we've ever dreamed of,

31:23.125 --> 31:25.750
just like our forefathers
prophesized, okay?

31:25.833 --> 31:27.791
Now, Geronimo, what do you got?

31:27.875 --> 31:30.708
Uh, tracking isn't an exact science.

31:30.791 --> 31:33.458
This is a handkerchief.
What do you think I am? A dog?

31:33.541 --> 31:36.750
[chuckles] Okay,
I know this is a trick question,

31:36.833 --> 31:40.083
so I'm gonna go
with my immediate impulse. Yes.

31:40.166 --> 31:41.583
Fuck you, dude. [sniffs]

31:41.666 --> 31:43.750
-Yeah, he's in there.
-[redcoat 1] Ello, guv'ner.

31:43.833 --> 31:46.208
-[redcoat 2] Ello, guv'ner.
-Ello, guv!

31:46.291 --> 31:48.166
[all] Ello, guv'ner.

31:48.250 --> 31:49.833
All right, that's a lot of men.

31:49.916 --> 31:52.166
And it's a sure bet
that there's even more inside.

31:52.250 --> 31:54.916
Wait, are we seriously
thinkin' about goin' in there?

31:55.000 --> 31:58.125
-Look at this place! It's a quagmire!
-[all] Guv'ner!

31:58.208 --> 32:00.958
Guys, we could be here for years
and accomplish nothing.

32:01.041 --> 32:04.125
You're right.
But we'd be accomplishing nothing…

32:04.750 --> 32:05.916
for America.

32:06.541 --> 32:08.458
Guys, I can't ask you
to go in there with me.

32:08.541 --> 32:09.375
Phew!

32:09.458 --> 32:11.666
-Yeah, good, because no.
-Great. Good luck.

32:11.750 --> 32:13.250
Whoa, whoa, wait, hold on.

32:13.333 --> 32:16.250
I thought I'd be all like,
"No, don't. I can do it."

32:16.333 --> 32:19.708
And then you guys would be like,
"No, I'll come, don't worry."

32:19.791 --> 32:23.291
I never know the right thing to say
when I'm tryin' to lead. This sucks!

32:23.375 --> 32:27.708
So, yeah, I guess I am.
I'm asking you to go in there with me.

32:29.500 --> 32:31.041
Will you please go in there with me?

32:31.625 --> 32:34.333
Huh, well, with a pep talk like that,
how could I say no?

32:34.416 --> 32:37.875
Pfft, whatever.
Let's just go kick some Redcoat ass!

32:37.958 --> 32:41.125
Wait, wait, wait! At least…
Just let me do an entrance thing.

32:41.208 --> 32:43.250
[redcoat] Guv'ner? [grunts]

32:43.333 --> 32:46.291
Ding dong! It's America, motherfucker!

32:46.375 --> 32:48.875
Oh, Georgie! Well, color me surprised.

32:48.958 --> 32:51.000
Oh, I'll color you fuckin' dead, Ben!

32:51.083 --> 32:52.875
[laughs] Bravo!

32:52.958 --> 32:55.833
Did you practice that line
in the car on your way here?

32:55.916 --> 32:57.250
What the fuck is a car?

32:57.333 --> 33:00.333
And, no, it was a rebuttal
to something that you just said!

33:00.416 --> 33:02.041
How could I have thought of it in advance

33:02.125 --> 33:04.750
if you said it just now
and I came up with the perfect rebuttal?

33:04.833 --> 33:06.416
Oh, pardon me.

33:06.500 --> 33:09.458
I forgot you aren't versed
in the gentlemanly art of debate,

33:09.541 --> 33:11.250
like your best friend, Abe Lincoln.

33:11.333 --> 33:15.916
Oh, or should I say ex-best friend?

33:16.000 --> 33:17.125
[laughs]

33:17.208 --> 33:18.875
-Because he's dead.
-Damn, he's good.

33:18.958 --> 33:20.583
-All right, fuck this.
-[glass shatters]

33:22.875 --> 33:26.416
-[motor revs]
-[yelling] For Abe!

33:26.500 --> 33:27.958
[objects clattering]

33:28.041 --> 33:30.833
-[Samuel] Yippie-kay-yay, motherfu-- Whoa!
-[electrical buzzing]

33:30.916 --> 33:33.166
-[Samuel] Watch it, witch!
-[Edison] You watch it, dick!

33:36.291 --> 33:38.333
[George] Yeah.
Well, that could've gone better.

33:38.416 --> 33:41.291
Ya think?
Edison almost got everybody killed!

33:41.375 --> 33:44.333
-Everybody almost got everybody killed!
-Where's Arnold?

33:44.416 --> 33:47.500
And where's Geronimo?
He smells like campfire.

33:52.541 --> 33:54.583
You carry an unusual scent for a man.

33:55.125 --> 33:57.083
Almost like you're
not a man at all, but a--

33:57.166 --> 33:58.208
[growls]

33:58.291 --> 33:59.375
[grunts]

33:59.458 --> 34:01.166
Stay and fight, you dick!

34:01.250 --> 34:03.166
Damn it! Oh, my God! Geronimo!

34:03.250 --> 34:04.541
That bastard bit me!

34:04.625 --> 34:06.916
It can't be.
I thought they were just a myth.

34:07.000 --> 34:10.333
The Navajo have
a name for their kind. Skinwalker.

34:10.416 --> 34:12.125
I won't live with this curse.

34:12.208 --> 34:14.041
-Hand me my ax.
-Are you sure?

34:14.125 --> 34:15.666
Does my grandfather shit in the woods?

34:15.750 --> 34:18.375
Um, I… Does he? I didn't know him.

34:18.458 --> 34:20.125
It's what we call bears.

34:21.000 --> 34:23.000
We call bears "grandfather."

34:23.083 --> 34:25.125
Fuck it, just give me my ax!

34:25.208 --> 34:26.500
[breathing heavily]

34:28.166 --> 34:29.333
[screams]

34:31.500 --> 34:33.916
Whoa, whoa, Geronimo!
What happened? Are you okay?

34:34.000 --> 34:35.333
Go! I'll take care of him.

34:35.416 --> 34:38.208
She's right, he's not important.
Arnold's getting away!

34:38.291 --> 34:39.541
[horse neighs]

34:39.625 --> 34:42.625
No! No. We never leave a man behind.

34:42.708 --> 34:45.500
Edison, dress that wound.
Paul, call your horse.

34:45.583 --> 34:47.666
Hey, Clyde!

34:47.750 --> 34:49.708
["Yankee And The Brave" playing]

34:52.083 --> 34:54.375
-That way!
-Run, Clyde, run!

35:00.000 --> 35:01.666
[explodes]

35:05.833 --> 35:07.041
[neighs]

35:10.583 --> 35:12.291
[sirens blaring]

35:31.041 --> 35:32.375
[explodes]

35:39.875 --> 35:41.083
[cackles]

35:47.541 --> 35:49.750
-Whoa, whoa, whoa!
-[hooves screeching]

35:58.416 --> 35:59.333
[neighs]

36:00.041 --> 36:03.166
Welcome to hell… acopter?

36:03.250 --> 36:06.291
I'm still working on it.
I don't love it, but I don't hate it.

36:09.833 --> 36:13.541
-[Edison] Paul, you were amazing.
-[Paul] Aw, thank you, human lady friend.

36:13.625 --> 36:16.875
And, Sam, your propensity
for murder is extraordinary.

36:16.958 --> 36:20.375
Thank you.
I took murder lessons from John Wick.

36:20.458 --> 36:22.458
-[gasps] The candle maker?
-Yeah!

36:22.541 --> 36:25.875
That dude is a fuckin' psycho! [laughs]

36:25.958 --> 36:27.583
Yo, check it. The carriage stopped.

36:27.666 --> 36:29.416
[George] But why would he stop here?

36:29.500 --> 36:30.833
The road to Delaware!

36:33.333 --> 36:35.583
Sea-Doo, bitches!

36:36.625 --> 36:39.416
Paul, can your sizable steed
clear that river?

36:39.500 --> 36:42.208
-Only one way to find out.
-[neighs]

36:43.791 --> 36:45.416
In God I trust.

36:45.500 --> 36:46.500
[neighs]

36:49.041 --> 36:51.416
[all] Whoa!

36:51.500 --> 36:52.625
[Samuel] Oh, shit.

36:53.583 --> 36:55.000
[all coughing]

36:55.083 --> 36:57.833
He shorted it, Paul.
Hey, Paul, he shorted it.

36:57.916 --> 37:01.083
Clyde! His natural buoyancy
can support us all!

37:01.166 --> 37:03.083
[George coughing] Jesus Christ!

37:03.166 --> 37:06.041
Did you know that your horse
could swim that fast?

37:06.125 --> 37:08.500
Oh, yeah, Clyde's a great swimmer.

37:08.583 --> 37:12.166
He's great at so many things.
So proud!

37:13.625 --> 37:14.625
[gasps]

37:15.958 --> 37:19.208
Thank you, Geronimo.
Your hair looks even better wet.

37:19.291 --> 37:21.625
Y'all a bunch of idiots.

37:21.708 --> 37:24.166
[sighs] This feels like the end…

37:24.250 --> 37:26.750
of the first act… of my life.

37:27.416 --> 37:28.791
All hope is lost.

37:29.500 --> 37:32.791
What do we even do now?
Where do we go from here?

37:32.875 --> 37:35.041
[gasps] Where we go isn't the question.

37:35.125 --> 37:37.208
The question is,

37:37.291 --> 37:40.500
do we bring an entree
or a fucking dessert?

37:43.125 --> 37:47.000
[Edison] Oh, guys,
Gettysburg is impossibly vast.

37:47.083 --> 37:50.541
Finding this address
is like finding a needle in a haystack.

37:50.625 --> 37:52.375
Yeah, Edison's right. Let's just give up.

37:52.458 --> 37:55.666
-That is not what I said.
-What? Dudes, look, we tried.

37:55.750 --> 37:58.916
One thing. We literally tried one thing.

37:59.000 --> 38:00.958
Yeah, and it didn't work.

38:01.041 --> 38:03.041
-[horn sounds]
-We all got wet, Edison. God!

38:03.125 --> 38:04.666
Look, this isn't fun anymore.

38:04.750 --> 38:06.958
Uh, I can fix that.

38:07.041 --> 38:09.083
Let's get hammered!

38:09.166 --> 38:13.500
Then, fuck it,
we hit the streets mob-rules style.

38:13.583 --> 38:16.458
Anyone we see who doesn't look like us,

38:16.541 --> 38:19.583
they see the bottom of our boots!

38:19.666 --> 38:20.916
Oh, my God.

38:21.000 --> 38:24.041
Okay, fine, no Indians this time.
Ooh, geez.

38:24.125 --> 38:27.333
Oh, my God. I don't know
how many times I have to tell you, Sam.

38:27.416 --> 38:30.500
-This is not India.
-Also, you're a fucking racist.

38:30.583 --> 38:33.166
Uh, no, Paul's the racist.

38:33.250 --> 38:35.416
He's the best horse racist
in the colonies.

38:35.500 --> 38:37.333
Yeah, I'm a great racist.

38:37.416 --> 38:38.791
Holy shit.

38:38.875 --> 38:40.666
-[plucking guitar string]
-[sighs]

38:40.750 --> 38:44.333
[singing] A… A… A… A… A…

38:44.416 --> 38:47.291
Who wants pizza rolls and purple stuff?

38:47.375 --> 38:51.000
-Oh, wow, Chief Geronimo!
-Just Geronimo is fine.

38:51.083 --> 38:53.500
-You're the famous renegade tracker.
-Sure.

38:53.583 --> 38:57.166
And [gasps] you're Thomas Edison,
the world-renowned scientist!

38:57.250 --> 38:58.541
[scoffs] The same.

38:58.625 --> 39:01.250
Wow, George, the team
is really shaping up nicely.

39:01.333 --> 39:04.208
Oh, no. No, we're not
a team anymore, Martha. We quit.

39:04.291 --> 39:06.458
-What?
-Besides, the revolution was Abe's thing.

39:06.541 --> 39:08.666
I tried to avenge him, but we blew it.

39:08.750 --> 39:11.208
Now, we're just gonna jam a bit
and slam some beers.

39:11.291 --> 39:12.875
This is a basic blues riff, guys.

39:12.958 --> 39:16.208
Just watch me for the changes.
All right, losers, let's party.

39:16.291 --> 39:20.333
No! George Bon Jovi Washington,
you do not get to party.

39:20.416 --> 39:22.833
-What?
-Would Abe want to party right now?

39:22.916 --> 39:24.375
Abe never wanted to party.

39:24.458 --> 39:28.583
Because he had goals, unrealized dreams.

39:28.666 --> 39:31.791
But you bet your ass
once those dreams were realized,

39:31.875 --> 39:34.791
he would've snorted a line
as long as the Magna Carta.

39:34.875 --> 39:37.375
Really? No. Abe? My Abe?

39:37.458 --> 39:39.208
Are you kidding? With that head?

39:39.291 --> 39:44.208
[laughs] Dude was all sinus.
He was made for the marching powder.

39:44.291 --> 39:45.500
Not how cocaine works.

39:45.583 --> 39:48.708
Now, those goals are your goals.

39:48.791 --> 39:52.666
Those unrealized dreams
are your unrealized dreams.

39:52.750 --> 39:55.125
That's the promise that you made, right?

39:55.208 --> 39:57.541
So, achieve those goals.

39:57.625 --> 39:59.458
Realize those dreams.

39:59.541 --> 40:03.333
And then, you can party
like a rich white man

40:03.416 --> 40:08.291
who will never face adversity
for the rest of his glorious life!

40:08.958 --> 40:11.416
You're right. I have to earn it.

40:11.500 --> 40:13.625
That is what Abe would want,

40:13.708 --> 40:16.291
that insane coke-hound! [chuckles]

40:16.375 --> 40:18.041
Guys, I've thought about it.

40:18.125 --> 40:20.166
I'm willing to give it another shot
if you are.

40:20.250 --> 40:21.541
-What do you say?
-Sure, man.

40:21.625 --> 40:22.750
Um, you're the one who quit.

40:22.833 --> 40:26.458
If we can find Arnold, we can force
the Gettysburg Address out of him.

40:26.541 --> 40:29.750
Oh, I'm sorry,
did none of you notice my fucking arm?

40:29.833 --> 40:32.000
Benedict Arnold is a werewolf!

40:32.625 --> 40:34.416
In some cultures, known as a skinwalker.

40:34.500 --> 40:37.833
He ain't givin' up shit unless
he thinks we're an actual threat to him.

40:37.916 --> 40:39.666
The only way to be
an actual threat to him--

40:39.750 --> 40:42.041
Is if we have a silver bullet.

40:42.125 --> 40:44.333
-Exactly.
-Wait, what are we doing again?

40:44.416 --> 40:47.125
A silver bullet?
Who could ever even make such a thing?

40:47.208 --> 40:48.458
I know a blacksmith.

40:48.541 --> 40:51.458
He made this armor
and I've never taken it off.

40:51.541 --> 40:54.291
Okay. Okay! We'll visit this blacksmith

40:54.375 --> 40:58.208
and he will discover the secret
of the impossible weapon we require.

40:58.291 --> 41:00.083
Because our cause is just!

41:00.166 --> 41:01.416
It is righteous!

41:01.500 --> 41:03.916
It is His will! His and Abe's!

41:04.000 --> 41:05.583
-And the Earth Mother's.
-Nope.

41:05.666 --> 41:07.625
-And Isaac Newton's.
-Nope. Just God's.

41:07.708 --> 41:10.041
I hold these truths to be self-evident.

41:10.125 --> 41:12.208
All for one and one for all!

41:12.291 --> 41:14.500
We will find the Gettysburg Address.

41:14.583 --> 41:15.708
[all] Huzzah!

41:15.791 --> 41:17.708
[Paul] Huzzah! Nope, too late.

41:19.833 --> 41:21.166
[clanking]

41:21.875 --> 41:22.708
[grunts]

41:22.791 --> 41:24.166
[hisses]

41:32.083 --> 41:35.041
-Smittay!
-[bell chimes]

41:37.083 --> 41:39.166
Damn! Fuck my life.

41:39.250 --> 41:40.708
We're friends.

41:40.791 --> 41:42.833
[birds chirping]

41:43.875 --> 41:46.166
Do I even wanna know
why you need a silver bullet?

41:46.250 --> 41:48.041
Best that you not know, Mr. Smith.

41:48.125 --> 41:49.666
Why do you keep calling me Mr. Smith?

41:49.750 --> 41:52.041
Well, Revere called you Black Smith.

41:52.125 --> 41:55.125
-Right, because I'm a blacksmith.
-Right. A Black Smith.

41:55.208 --> 41:56.750
-A blacksmith.
-Black Smith.

41:56.833 --> 41:58.750
I'm a smith who works with metal,

41:58.833 --> 42:02.833
which oxidizes during
the heating process and turns black.

42:02.916 --> 42:05.500
-So, you're a Smith.
-Exactly.

42:05.583 --> 42:07.083
-Of the Baltimore Smiths?
-[sighs]

42:07.166 --> 42:08.750
Just tell me what you need it for.

42:08.833 --> 42:11.500
It'll be used to free the colonies.
Let's just leave it at that.

42:11.583 --> 42:14.250
Oh, you're talking about the Brits.

42:14.333 --> 42:17.416
Shit, why didn't you say so?
I'm definitely down for that.

42:17.500 --> 42:19.208
-You are?
-Fuck, yeah!

42:19.291 --> 42:20.833
I mean, don't get it twisted.

42:20.916 --> 42:23.291
I definitely do not trust
you motherfuckers.

42:23.875 --> 42:25.125
You three, especially.

42:25.208 --> 42:27.375
But fuck, man, I hate the British.

42:27.458 --> 42:29.250
Why, what have the fun police done to you?

42:29.333 --> 42:31.416
Look around. I'm a small business owner.

42:31.500 --> 42:34.208
What's a small business owner's
greatest enemy?

42:34.291 --> 42:36.041
-Large businesses?
-Thin profit margins?

42:36.125 --> 42:38.708
-Rising lube costs?
-White people stealing everything you own.

42:38.958 --> 42:40.666
-Having a squirrel for a friend?
-No.

42:40.750 --> 42:42.458
-Staff turnover?
-Tesla being a bitch?

42:42.541 --> 42:46.125
-Not getting drunk at lunch?
-White people stealing everything you own.

42:46.208 --> 42:47.708
Constant instinct to second-guess

42:47.791 --> 42:50.250
having risked your savings
on unproven business acumen?

42:50.333 --> 42:53.041
-No, it's taxes.
-Taxes. Correct.

42:53.125 --> 42:56.791
Small business taxes. And what's
the big knock against the British?

42:56.875 --> 42:59.125
-Something about taxation!
-Exactly.

42:59.208 --> 43:01.875
You'll help us? You'll craft
the silver bullet free of charge?

43:01.958 --> 43:04.250
What? Are you white motherfuckers crazy?

43:04.333 --> 43:07.000
I just told you
I'm a small business owner.

43:07.083 --> 43:09.625
You think I'm gonna
give you silver for free?

43:09.708 --> 43:11.291
Well, we don't have silver.

43:11.375 --> 43:13.333
The British seized it all
when they got here--

43:13.416 --> 43:16.625
Spoons. Teaspoons. I remember.

43:16.708 --> 43:18.750
Why do you think that shit's so expensive?

43:18.833 --> 43:21.875
Okay. Well, how much
do we need for, like, one bullet?

43:21.958 --> 43:24.333
-A metric shit-ton.
-For one bullet?

43:24.416 --> 43:28.000
Oh, I'm sorry.
Are you a fucking metallurgist like me?

43:28.083 --> 43:30.458
-That's, like, a thousand spoons!
-Three thousand.

43:30.541 --> 43:32.500
It's a metric shit-ton.

43:32.583 --> 43:35.541
Where are we gonna get
3,000 spoons overnight, bro?

43:35.625 --> 43:36.458
Well…

43:36.541 --> 43:39.166
[ship horn sounds]

43:39.250 --> 43:42.083
[blacksmith] May I present,
the year's biggest tea party.

43:42.166 --> 43:45.041
You need silver spoons,
you need to get aboard that ship.

43:45.125 --> 43:47.458
Wait a minute.
How did you know about this?

43:48.500 --> 43:50.916
[Samuel] What's up with
these assholes and flyers?

43:51.000 --> 43:54.458
Well, it's a great way to communicate
with a widespread audience,

43:54.541 --> 43:58.208
much like direct mail or the Pony Express,
where my brother does not work.

43:58.291 --> 44:01.625
-[grunts] All right. Shall we?
-Wait, wait, wait. Wait!

44:04.166 --> 44:05.625
-We need a plan.
-Why?

44:05.708 --> 44:08.583
Well, last time we didn't have one
and things got shitty.

44:08.666 --> 44:10.333
-Huh?
-Yeah, Geronimo lost his arm.

44:10.416 --> 44:13.916
-No, he lost like three-fifths of an arm.
-[scoffs] Seriously?

44:14.000 --> 44:15.958
Oh, thoughts and prayers.

44:16.041 --> 44:19.250
Look, good leaders like Abe
have a plan for everything.

44:19.333 --> 44:21.875
-All right, His Leadership, let's hear it.
-Okay.

44:21.958 --> 44:24.583
So, Mr. Smith, you'll be the lookout.

44:24.666 --> 44:26.791
-[blacksmith laughs] Nope.
-What?

44:26.875 --> 44:31.083
You want me, a Black dude,
to sit here in the dark, alone,

44:31.166 --> 44:33.458
to play lookout for you
while you break the law?

44:33.541 --> 44:37.500
Oh, hell no! I hate the British
but I ain't lookin' to get killed.

44:37.583 --> 44:40.458
So, y'all are on your own
to get that silver.

44:40.541 --> 44:42.875
But if you do get it,
I'll make your little bullet.

44:42.958 --> 44:45.041
All right. Then…

44:45.125 --> 44:46.375
here's the plan.

44:46.458 --> 44:50.416
Geronimo, you'll be the lookout.
Are you cool with being the lookout?

44:50.500 --> 44:52.958
I mean, if my choice is to be the lookout

44:53.041 --> 44:56.666
or have one of you looking out for me,
yeah, I'll be the lookout.

44:56.750 --> 45:00.708
Great. Okay. Edison, you'll pose as
the wife of an officer already on board.

45:00.791 --> 45:04.833
[groans] This is taking too long.
Let's just dress as those guys.

45:04.916 --> 45:07.375
[all] Ello, guv.

45:07.458 --> 45:09.833
Well, technically, that is a plan.

45:11.875 --> 45:14.000
Just technically, a very bad plan.

45:14.083 --> 45:18.916
Ha! I told you a jail would be
a better use of space than lifeboats.

45:19.000 --> 45:21.208
Hey, at least we got on board,
right, guys?

45:21.291 --> 45:24.250
I consider this mission accomplished.
Ooh, we should get a banner.

45:24.333 --> 45:28.375
Ugh, shockingly, Sam's not wrong.
We can still make this work.

45:28.458 --> 45:30.666
I've taken note
of how often the guards go on rounds.

45:30.750 --> 45:32.666
-If we lay low for a few hours--
-No!

45:32.750 --> 45:34.875
Enough with all of the planning!

45:34.958 --> 45:38.125
Did Magellan have a plan
when he circumnavigated the globe?

45:38.208 --> 45:39.333
-[all] No!
-[Edison] Yes.

45:39.416 --> 45:40.750
That took a lot of preparation.

45:40.833 --> 45:46.000
We'll set our course for freedom
using only our wits as our guide.

45:46.083 --> 45:48.916
Mr. Revere, tear down that wall.

45:49.000 --> 45:50.458
[Paul] Whee!

45:53.958 --> 45:55.333
What is this place?

45:55.416 --> 45:57.666
I don't know, but don't touch any--

45:57.750 --> 45:58.958
Ooh, oops.

46:10.750 --> 46:14.416
They're steeping the colonists in tea!

46:14.500 --> 46:18.041
Turning them British.
James, you sick bastard!

46:18.125 --> 46:20.541
Look, as far as I can tell,
this is a test run.

46:20.625 --> 46:23.375
James is up to something bigger
than crushing the revolution.

46:23.458 --> 46:25.916
Maybe even…
Oh, fuck! I don't even want to say it!

46:26.000 --> 46:27.750
-Just say it.
-Something global.

46:27.833 --> 46:28.708
[all gasp]

46:28.791 --> 46:31.750
-That means…
-There are global stakes now.

46:31.833 --> 46:34.416
Good God!
Can you figure out what he's planning?

46:34.500 --> 46:37.291
Yeah, I think I can.
If I can just hack the mainframe.

46:37.375 --> 46:40.125
Great. Guys, gather as many
silver spoons as you can.

46:40.208 --> 46:44.291
In the meantime, I'll get these
hardworking Americans out of these tubes!

46:44.375 --> 46:45.625
[Edison] George! No!

46:46.541 --> 46:50.708
No! I had almost downloaded the plan.

46:50.791 --> 46:53.333
-Uh, guys, we gotta go.
-Yep.

46:53.416 --> 46:56.000
Totally right.
Grab spoons, guys. Quick, let's go.

46:57.166 --> 46:58.833
[exploding]

47:01.666 --> 47:03.000
[indistinct shouting]

47:05.416 --> 47:06.750
[screams]

47:09.958 --> 47:12.708
-[Paul] Oh, no.
-Oh, my God, the humanity.

47:12.791 --> 47:15.083
This is bad. This is so bad.

47:15.166 --> 47:16.916
Those poor boat people.

47:17.000 --> 47:20.708
Look, if anybody asks,
the Titanic hit an iceberg.

47:20.791 --> 47:23.250
We were never here, baby.

47:27.333 --> 47:28.666
[sighs]

47:28.750 --> 47:31.791
It's hopeless, Martha.
At this rate, I'll never avenge Abe.

47:31.875 --> 47:33.708
And see his dream through, don't forget.

47:33.791 --> 47:36.458
-That's the whole second part.
-I tried.

47:36.541 --> 47:40.375
I tried to be a leader like him, Martha.
It's just not working.

47:40.458 --> 47:43.666
Oh, George. Abe was a great leader,
but you can't copy him.

47:43.750 --> 47:46.458
You must find
your own style of leadership.

47:46.541 --> 47:50.583
Maybe something with less planning.
Something more free-spirited, like you.

47:50.666 --> 47:53.333
I know. I just wish
I realized that before we…

47:53.416 --> 47:56.458
Before the Titanic hit that iceberg.

47:56.541 --> 47:58.333
Yes. What a tragedy.

47:58.416 --> 48:00.416
Right? Such a tragedy!

48:00.500 --> 48:05.333
It feels like, for every step forward,
we just take two steps back. John 3:16.

48:05.416 --> 48:09.041
Then, let's focus on the positive, huh?
What was tonight's step forward?

48:09.125 --> 48:10.875
-I got these spoons.
-[spoons jingling]

48:10.958 --> 48:14.291
Oh, that's great, George.
And are they, like, for something?

48:14.375 --> 48:17.875
Yeah, but they're still useless
without the Gettysburg Address.

48:17.958 --> 48:21.041
[sighs] The tirelessness
with which you've pursued your quest

48:21.125 --> 48:23.000
has betrayed your confidence in it.

48:23.083 --> 48:25.333
Perhaps a quick HJ to help you sleep.

48:25.416 --> 48:27.583
Generous, but I need to earn it.

48:27.666 --> 48:29.250
Then, for now, rest, my love.

48:29.333 --> 48:32.083
Clear your head.
It's always darkest before the dawn.

48:32.166 --> 48:35.083
-John 3:16?
-I don't think so, champ.

48:35.958 --> 48:38.250
For now, rest, my love. Clear your head.

48:38.333 --> 48:40.250
It's always darkest before the dawn.

48:41.291 --> 48:42.208
[gasps]

48:42.291 --> 48:43.750
Where am I?

48:43.833 --> 48:45.875
[Abe] Don't worry, George. You're safe.

48:45.958 --> 48:49.708
Abe? Abe, is that you?
I can't see. Everything's so bright.

48:49.791 --> 48:53.333
Oh, that's me. Sorry, I was trying
to make this seem more impressive.

48:53.833 --> 48:56.708
It's great to see you, Abe.
But what is this place?

48:56.791 --> 48:59.833
[echoing] It's your dream world, George.

48:59.916 --> 49:00.958
Is it?

49:01.041 --> 49:04.583
Can I ask a question, real quick?
Why is my dream world so shitty?

49:04.666 --> 49:07.041
[chuckles] Well, we ran out of money.

49:07.125 --> 49:08.666
-My dream ran out of money?
-Sure.

49:08.750 --> 49:12.500
Yeah. Look, I've been told by the,
you know, "dream producers,"

49:12.583 --> 49:15.291
that we could use this money
more effectively elsewhere.

49:15.375 --> 49:19.875
Like in an epic ending battle happening
sometime in the next 30 minutes or so.

49:19.958 --> 49:21.583
Okay, well, what were you gonna do?

49:21.666 --> 49:23.708
Oh, I had this whole idea worked out.

49:23.791 --> 49:26.500
-You were gonna fight a dream-hydra.
-Whoa, that's cool.

49:26.583 --> 49:29.875
I know. And it was made up
of all of King James' rules.

49:29.958 --> 49:32.375
And for every rule you cut down,
another appeared.

49:32.458 --> 49:33.708
-Rah!
-[George] Ooh!

49:33.791 --> 49:35.958
-That's a nice metaphor, dude!
-Thanks, bro.

49:36.041 --> 49:37.958
And it was all about how the revolution

49:38.041 --> 49:40.958
is about more
than just breaking the king's rules.

49:41.041 --> 49:43.000
It's also about your son.

49:43.083 --> 49:46.083
-What? I'm havin' a boy?
-[laughs] Yeah!

49:46.166 --> 49:49.208
Boom! Sex, bitch! Oh, shit! Yeah!

49:49.291 --> 49:51.083
Either way would be cool. Girls are cool.

49:51.166 --> 49:54.500
Yeah. Yeah, it's a son, though.
He's the future.

49:54.583 --> 49:57.875
Him and all the sons
and daughters of this great nation,

49:57.958 --> 50:01.041
no matter what they look like
or where they come from.

50:01.125 --> 50:03.250
Be a leader for them, George.

50:03.333 --> 50:05.291
A leader for all people!

50:05.375 --> 50:07.666
I get it. I get it, Abe.

50:07.750 --> 50:09.416
But I would've got it a lot better

50:09.500 --> 50:11.666
if I was kicking an ass
of a giant dream-hydra,

50:11.750 --> 50:13.666
but I'm just saying, I get it. I got it.

50:13.750 --> 50:15.458
Agreed. But don't worry, George.

50:15.541 --> 50:17.333
There's plenty of fighting left to do.

50:17.416 --> 50:18.750
Oh, and one more thing.

50:18.833 --> 50:21.125
What is it, old chum?
You can tell me anything.

50:21.208 --> 50:24.166
When your wife
offers you a hand job, you take it.

50:24.250 --> 50:25.750
-[Martha] George!
-Martha!

50:25.833 --> 50:28.333
-[groans] George!
-Martha!

50:28.416 --> 50:31.000
Oh, don't worry about her, Georgie.

50:31.083 --> 50:35.583
She'll be quite not well taken care of,
if you catch my drift.

50:35.666 --> 50:39.291
I don't. But you were on the Titanic.
You should be dead.

50:39.375 --> 50:41.916
I mean, I heard you were on the Titanic.

50:42.000 --> 50:44.416
That's what I heard
from someone who was there,

50:44.500 --> 50:47.666
while I was here… reading… this book.

50:47.750 --> 50:48.875
The Graps of Wreath.

50:48.958 --> 50:51.250
Yes, well,
I'm an excellent swimmer, dickhead.

50:51.333 --> 50:53.000
You should've done your research.

50:53.083 --> 50:54.166
Thanks for the tip.

50:54.250 --> 50:56.333
When Edison invents
the Internet next year,

50:56.416 --> 50:59.708
I'll make sure
to edit your Wikipedia page myself.

50:59.791 --> 51:05.500
"Benedict Arnold, great swimmer
and a total fucking asswipe."

51:05.583 --> 51:07.458
Well, I'll just change it back.

51:07.541 --> 51:10.083
No, you won't, because you'll be dead!

51:10.166 --> 51:12.000
-[motor sputters]
-Huh?

51:12.125 --> 51:13.041
What?

51:13.125 --> 51:15.458
Well, maybe
after she invents the Internet,

51:15.541 --> 51:20.125
your friend Edison can invent chainsaws
that don't require gasoline. [laughs]

51:20.208 --> 51:25.458
You sucked the gas out
of my arm chainsaws while I was sleeping?

51:25.541 --> 51:28.958
Jesus Christ,
what kind of psychopath are you?

51:29.041 --> 51:31.375
The worst kind.

51:31.875 --> 51:33.208
Whatever you take that to mean.

51:33.291 --> 51:35.208
Take her to the Gettysburg Address.

51:35.291 --> 51:36.958
-[Martha] George, no!
-Martha!

51:37.041 --> 51:40.583
Oh, my, Georgie,
I just realized we woke you up.

51:41.166 --> 51:44.458
-Please allow us to recompense.
-[grunts]

51:46.416 --> 51:49.458
[Paul] Last night was bad news,
human friends.

51:49.541 --> 51:53.750
Yeah, bad news for the fun police.
Eat a dick, Titanic!

51:53.833 --> 51:56.875
-[laughs]
-Right! Yes! Cool, cool, cool.

51:56.958 --> 52:01.125
And I guess the entire harbor ecosystem
can just eat a dick, too, right?

52:01.208 --> 52:04.583
I mean… Yes, 100%.

52:04.666 --> 52:08.958
Alarm! Alarm! Alarm! Alarm! Alarm!

52:09.041 --> 52:10.500
-Are you okay?
-George! What is it?

52:10.583 --> 52:12.000
Arnold kidnapped Martha!

52:12.083 --> 52:14.083
-Oh, no!
-It sucks when they steal your wife!

52:14.166 --> 52:15.250
And she's pregnant!

52:15.333 --> 52:17.333
-What?
-Congratulations, that's a beautiful gift!

52:17.416 --> 52:19.791
Thanks! I'm sorry
this is how I'm telling you,

52:19.875 --> 52:21.458
but we appreciate your support!

52:21.541 --> 52:23.458
We're already
on waiting lists for preschool.

52:23.541 --> 52:26.875
Hey, man. Maybe you need
to take some time for yourself.

52:26.958 --> 52:28.916
It's a lot, emotionally. I would know.

52:29.000 --> 52:31.583
No, that's exactly what I don't need.

52:31.666 --> 52:34.375
The old George
would just party these woes away.

52:34.458 --> 52:37.833
But not me.
This just adds fuel to my fuckin' fire.

52:37.916 --> 52:39.291
Hell yeah, man!

52:39.375 --> 52:41.541
Ben said he's keeping her
at the Gettysburg Address.

52:41.625 --> 52:44.791
Which we still don't have.
George, I'm sorry to say,

52:44.875 --> 52:46.958
but we've tried
everything to crack this code.

52:47.041 --> 52:49.208
-Code…
-I don't know what else we can do.

52:50.208 --> 52:52.958
-Code… Oh! Holy shit!
-What?

52:53.041 --> 52:54.416
[George] Not many people know this,

52:54.500 --> 52:57.666
but Abe wasn't
just America's premier celebrity chef.

52:57.750 --> 53:00.250
He was also
its most capable cryptographer.

53:00.333 --> 53:01.458
Plip-plopipher?

53:01.541 --> 53:05.250
Cryptographer. You know, someone
who crafts and solves codes and ciphers.

53:05.333 --> 53:06.875
[chuckling] Yeah, a plip-plopipher.

53:06.958 --> 53:09.958
That's what I said.
We're saying the same thing.

53:10.041 --> 53:13.125
Exactly. Which means
that Abe's final edict,

53:13.208 --> 53:18.291
that I name our freed country America,
was itself likely a cipher.

53:18.375 --> 53:21.791
Hidden within the words
of America, my friends,

53:21.875 --> 53:24.500
is the Gettysburg Address.

53:24.583 --> 53:26.625
I don't know, seems like kind of a leap.

53:26.708 --> 53:28.875
But I'll need some time to crack the code.

53:28.958 --> 53:31.583
In the meantime, someone must
run the spoons to Black Smith.

53:31.666 --> 53:33.375
[all at once] Not it!

53:33.458 --> 53:36.500
-All right, Chief, that's you.
-What the fuck just happened?

53:36.583 --> 53:39.833
Did I just lose a game that
white people didn't explain the rules to?

53:39.916 --> 53:41.666
I can't carry all the silver.

53:41.750 --> 53:44.958
-I only got the one arm.
-[laughing] And whose fault is that?

53:45.041 --> 53:47.625
That would be yours.
For screwing up Vietnam.

53:47.708 --> 53:51.250
What are you talking about?
We won Vietnam.

53:51.333 --> 53:55.958
[sighs] Actually, if it gives me some time
away from you, yeah, I'll do it.

53:56.041 --> 53:59.666
-You are a good man, Chief Geronimo.
-[Geronimo] Just Geronimo.

53:59.750 --> 54:01.125
The rest of you, come with me.

54:01.208 --> 54:03.916
I know the perfect place
to work on Abe's cipher.

54:08.583 --> 54:10.333
Ugh, come on.

54:15.166 --> 54:17.083
[King James] You left Washington alive.

54:17.166 --> 54:20.458
[Benedict] Uh, yes,
a calculated risk, my liege.

54:20.541 --> 54:22.291
Instead of trimming one thorn,

54:22.375 --> 54:25.916
we may soon be in position
to wipe out the whole damn bush.

54:27.666 --> 54:29.666
[King James] And kidnapping his wife?

54:29.750 --> 54:32.250
You're not worried that will motivate him?

54:32.333 --> 54:34.375
Oh, I'm counting on it.

54:34.458 --> 54:38.250
Still, we should expedite my… Your plan.

54:38.333 --> 54:41.500
Very well. Send me the head engineer.

54:43.708 --> 54:45.458
You wanted to see me, Your Majesty?

54:45.541 --> 54:48.250
There's been a slight change of plan.

54:48.333 --> 54:51.791
We'll need my weapon operational
sooner than anticipated.

54:51.875 --> 54:53.500
How much sooner, Your Majesty?

54:53.583 --> 54:55.166
You tell me.

54:55.250 --> 54:56.916
If we work around the clock,

54:57.000 --> 54:59.041
we could probably
have it ready in three weeks?

55:02.625 --> 55:05.416
-[gulps]
-[whistle blows]

55:05.500 --> 55:08.958
Please, Your Majesty, Your Highness.
I can do it faster.

55:12.166 --> 55:14.291
Ah, thank God.

55:16.166 --> 55:18.625
-[gasps]
-[shrieks]

55:19.958 --> 55:21.125
My foot!

55:21.208 --> 55:22.625
Most impressive.

55:22.708 --> 55:24.916
[screams]

55:25.000 --> 55:27.666
Manchester, come to Daddy.

55:27.750 --> 55:29.541
Oh, look at the good boy.

55:29.666 --> 55:32.416
Oh, look, you have
a little engineer on your face.

55:32.500 --> 55:34.250
Well, I guess I do, too, now.

55:34.333 --> 55:37.291
Don't I? Don't I? Yes!

55:37.375 --> 55:39.208
-[kisses]
-Uh, okay.

55:39.291 --> 55:42.083
I'll have Engineering
redouble their efforts.

55:42.166 --> 55:44.125
See that you do, Arnold.

55:44.208 --> 55:46.541
Whether or not you succeed with your plan,

55:46.625 --> 55:48.875
and in case it wasn't clear,
I'm not holding my breath,

55:48.958 --> 55:51.041
Washington is now marching inexorably

55:51.125 --> 55:54.083
into the gnashing maw
of the most diabolical war machine

55:54.166 --> 55:55.666
the world has ever known.

55:55.750 --> 55:58.458
And he doesn't even see it coming.

55:58.541 --> 56:02.125
-[laughs maniacally]
-Yes. They never do.

56:04.166 --> 56:08.208
Uh, George? I thought you said
you had a safe place to work.

56:08.291 --> 56:10.833
-What? This looks good to me.
-Thank you, Paul.

56:10.916 --> 56:14.291
But this isn't the place I had in mind.
That is.

56:14.375 --> 56:16.541
-[all exclaim]
-[Paul] It got even better!

56:18.583 --> 56:20.625
[George] Abe, I'm home.

56:21.416 --> 56:24.291
-[hisses]
-[exclaims] Pardon me, ma'am.

56:27.958 --> 56:31.375
Oh, my gord, horse toys! Whee!

56:41.250 --> 56:42.541
George?

56:42.625 --> 56:44.416
-George, are you okay, buddy?
-[sniffles]

56:44.500 --> 56:45.833
Yes, I am.

56:45.916 --> 56:48.666
But I need to be one with Abe now.

56:48.750 --> 56:52.541
I have to get inside of his head
if I hope to crack this code.

56:53.833 --> 56:55.000
Okay.

56:56.958 --> 56:57.875
Come on, come on!

56:59.625 --> 57:01.166
Confirm! Please confirm!

57:01.750 --> 57:03.000
We are cruisin'!

57:03.833 --> 57:05.625
Oh, yeah! [chuckles]

57:08.125 --> 57:10.750
Next and next. Next. Too easy.

57:10.833 --> 57:14.333
No, no, don't. No, no. Yes!
Reset 30%, please!

57:14.416 --> 57:16.000
Fuck no! I'm fucked.

57:16.333 --> 57:17.208
No, fuck!

57:19.083 --> 57:21.375
I am rusty, rusty.

57:21.458 --> 57:24.333
Okay, at the hands of this guy is you.

57:25.125 --> 57:26.250
Eternal destruction.

57:27.541 --> 57:29.041
Quick, quick, quick! Thank you.

57:29.125 --> 57:30.958
Return. Return. Yes!

57:31.041 --> 57:33.208
Three, two, one. Go!

57:33.291 --> 57:34.500
Come on. Yeah!

57:35.291 --> 57:37.000
Whoo! Yeah!

57:37.083 --> 57:38.458
You've been hacked, bro!

57:42.083 --> 57:45.000
So, what are you going to do
when this is all over, huh?

57:45.083 --> 57:46.458
You got family somewhere?

57:46.541 --> 57:47.750
Clyde is my family.

57:47.833 --> 57:51.416
No, I know, but like,
you know, people family, friends?

57:51.500 --> 57:53.000
That's why I'm doing this.

57:53.083 --> 57:57.541
You started a war against the most
powerful country on Earth to make friends?

57:57.625 --> 58:00.541
Yes. Yes, I did.
I never had people friends.

58:00.625 --> 58:02.541
Oh, Paul. You have one now.

58:02.625 --> 58:04.666
Thank you. Why do you wanna make war?

58:04.750 --> 58:07.916
They're mean to you
and they disrespect you, like a mule.

58:08.000 --> 58:09.916
Well, George means well.

58:10.000 --> 58:12.083
Sam disrespects me, but he's an idiot.

58:12.166 --> 58:15.666
Listen, lions don't concern themselves
with the opinions of sheep.

58:15.750 --> 58:20.000
Well, I'm friends with a lot of sheep
and, boy, are they opinionated.

58:20.083 --> 58:22.500
-Oh, I just meant--
-[mimics sheep bleating]

58:22.583 --> 58:23.625
That's how sheep talk.

58:23.708 --> 58:27.125
Look, I'm doing this
because I want science for everyone.

58:27.208 --> 58:30.791
Without fear of punishment
or persecution or even judgment.

58:30.875 --> 58:33.375
Problem is,
the rich white assholes that run the joint

58:33.458 --> 58:36.000
keep telling everyone
