-Well, we have the high ground.

1:12:23.875 --> 1:12:25.916
You have more than the high ground.

1:12:26.000 --> 1:12:28.625
Geronimo! Blacksmith!
We thought you deserted.

1:12:28.708 --> 1:12:33.000
Thought about it, like, really hard,
then started going in the other direction.

1:12:33.083 --> 1:12:35.958
Even booked an Air T&P
on the opposite side of town.

1:12:36.041 --> 1:12:38.375
But despite my better judgment,

1:12:38.458 --> 1:12:40.791
I ate the deposit and decided to come.

1:12:41.333 --> 1:12:43.166
Because this is my land

1:12:43.250 --> 1:12:46.333
and I don't need
anybody's permission to defend it.

1:12:46.416 --> 1:12:49.000
And Mr. Smith,
you'll join the fight as well?

1:12:49.083 --> 1:12:51.708
I figured, if we're gonna end up
with an old white dude in charge,

1:12:51.791 --> 1:12:54.291
we could do a hell of
a lot worse than you, George Washington.

1:12:54.375 --> 1:12:56.125
You're one of the good-ish ones.

1:12:57.125 --> 1:12:59.500
All that silver… for one bullet.

1:12:59.583 --> 1:13:01.708
Yeah, so you better make it count.

1:13:01.791 --> 1:13:04.291
We will, and we'll do it in style.

1:13:04.375 --> 1:13:05.250
[Samuel] Yeah.

1:13:05.333 --> 1:13:08.166
I commissioned Betsy Ross
and Tim Gunn to make these last night.

1:13:08.250 --> 1:13:10.291
Tim Gunn? Sounds like a badass.

1:13:10.375 --> 1:13:14.750
My dream, as silly as it seems now,
was that after our victory today,

1:13:14.833 --> 1:13:17.250
this design
would become a national symbol.

1:13:17.333 --> 1:13:19.583
The first ever American flag.

1:13:19.666 --> 1:13:23.666
-A symbol of our indomitable spirit.
-Of our thirst for knowledge!

1:13:23.750 --> 1:13:26.250
Of our tireless quest to kick ass!

1:13:26.333 --> 1:13:28.583
And, and! I'm just spitballing here,

1:13:28.666 --> 1:13:31.333
but maybe this style of blouse
will become the uniform

1:13:31.416 --> 1:13:34.291
of the first ever
American national pastime.

1:13:34.375 --> 1:13:37.375
It'll be like cricket,
but with actual rules.

1:13:37.458 --> 1:13:40.208
And you won't even
have to be athletic to participate.

1:13:40.291 --> 1:13:43.000
-Or have two arms.
-And women can play, too.

1:13:43.083 --> 1:13:45.166
You know, don't…
Let's not get sidetracked.

1:13:45.250 --> 1:13:46.500
Hark, the national bird!

1:13:46.583 --> 1:13:48.416
[Geronimo] You took everything else.

1:13:48.500 --> 1:13:51.333
You know what we need now?
A national song.

1:13:51.416 --> 1:13:52.958
I believe you mean…

1:13:56.333 --> 1:13:58.291
a national anthem.

1:13:58.375 --> 1:13:59.541
[eagle screeches]

1:14:08.541 --> 1:14:14.958
♪ If I leave here tomorrow ♪

1:14:16.750 --> 1:14:21.166
♪ Would you still remember me? ♪

1:14:24.416 --> 1:14:31.250
♪ For I must be traveling on now ♪

1:14:32.750 --> 1:14:36.916
♪ 'Cause there's too many places
I've got to see ♪

1:14:41.125 --> 1:14:47.125
♪ 'Cause I'm as free as a bird now ♪

1:14:49.208 --> 1:14:54.166
[crowd joins in]
♪ And this bird you cannot change ♪

1:14:54.833 --> 1:14:56.375
[vocalizing]

1:14:57.125 --> 1:15:03.458
[all] ♪ Lord help me, I can't change ♪

1:15:12.041 --> 1:15:13.541
-[thunder rumbling]
-[growling]

1:15:14.833 --> 1:15:17.291
[Thomas] This is so beautiful, George!

1:15:18.458 --> 1:15:20.958
[George] I know, it rocks, right?
I wrote it last night.

1:15:21.041 --> 1:15:22.708
I'm gonna request that song

1:15:22.791 --> 1:15:26.666
at every party
from now until the end of time.

1:15:26.750 --> 1:15:28.500
No. No, not the song.

1:15:29.125 --> 1:15:30.875
The Americans!

1:15:30.958 --> 1:15:33.458
[gasps] They came. It worked!

1:15:33.541 --> 1:15:34.625
What worked, G-Dub?

1:15:34.708 --> 1:15:36.750
I found an old note from Abe last night.

1:15:36.833 --> 1:15:39.875
And he said he wished
he had a million friends like me.

1:15:39.958 --> 1:15:43.916
And that's when I realized,
I can have a million friends.

1:15:44.000 --> 1:15:45.000
[all cheering]

1:15:45.083 --> 1:15:51.166
Oh! Why settle for 20 bros
when you could have a million,

1:15:51.250 --> 1:15:52.666
no matter how different they look.

1:15:52.750 --> 1:15:55.791
Exactly! Sam, that's the American way!

1:15:55.875 --> 1:15:57.791
Hey, guys. Did ya hear?

1:15:57.875 --> 1:16:01.250
I'm not racist anymore! I'm doin' it!

1:16:01.333 --> 1:16:02.250
Super.

1:16:02.333 --> 1:16:04.333
George, how did you do this?

1:16:04.416 --> 1:16:06.500
How did you reach
this many people overnight?

1:16:06.583 --> 1:16:10.916
I remembered something
one of my friends told me about flyers.

1:16:11.583 --> 1:16:14.666
They're a great way to communicate
with a widespread audience.

1:16:16.458 --> 1:16:20.166
I spent all night distributing these
all over this great land,

1:16:21.000 --> 1:16:23.125
from sea to shining sea.

1:16:23.208 --> 1:16:25.708
[Thomas] That's thousands of miles!
How did you--

1:16:25.791 --> 1:16:29.666
Oh, I had a little help
from the fastest racist in the colonies!

1:16:29.750 --> 1:16:30.958
[all] Whoa!

1:16:31.041 --> 1:16:33.875
-[Samuel] What have they done to you?
-[Geronimo] Does that hurt?

1:16:33.958 --> 1:16:37.375
[in robotic voice] The British are coming…
to get their asses kicked!

1:16:37.458 --> 1:16:41.666
Heh. Well, I am just glad
that we got the band back together.

1:16:41.750 --> 1:16:45.125
All right, everybody, come on!
Grab an AR-15.

1:16:45.208 --> 1:16:48.416
These little death machines here
are gonna even the odds for us.

1:16:48.500 --> 1:16:51.541
But once the war is over though,
okay, I definitely need them back.

1:16:51.625 --> 1:16:53.041
Yeah, man. No problem.

1:16:53.875 --> 1:16:57.958
Yeah, they're just way too dangerous
for civilians to keep. Am I right?

1:16:58.041 --> 1:16:59.875
That is completely reasonable.

1:17:01.708 --> 1:17:04.375
What in God's name are we waiting for?

1:17:04.458 --> 1:17:06.250
Why are we not attacking?

1:17:06.333 --> 1:17:08.208
Beggin' your pardon, me lord,

1:17:08.291 --> 1:17:12.625
the Americans was just changing their kits
into the stars and stripes, see?

1:17:12.708 --> 1:17:14.916
Then they sang a song for a bit, yeah.

1:17:15.000 --> 1:17:18.333
Now it looks like they're settlin'
some personal differences.

1:17:18.416 --> 1:17:19.583
Shan't be long.

1:17:19.666 --> 1:17:22.291
We don't have to wait
for them to get dressed.

1:17:22.375 --> 1:17:23.791
Attack, you idiots!

1:17:23.875 --> 1:17:26.458
Copy that, Command.
Commencing bombardment.

1:17:29.916 --> 1:17:33.500
Now, let's go start a fucking revolution!

1:17:33.583 --> 1:17:34.541
Kick it!

1:17:36.666 --> 1:17:40.458
Tread on them!
Tread the fuck all over them!

1:17:40.541 --> 1:17:42.416
[rock song playing]

1:17:54.458 --> 1:17:55.666
[yelling]

1:18:32.166 --> 1:18:33.000
[yelps]

1:18:35.375 --> 1:18:36.208
Oh, no.

1:18:54.333 --> 1:18:56.000
[eagles screeching]

1:18:58.291 --> 1:18:59.708
Me-ronimo!

1:19:04.708 --> 1:19:06.458
Edison, give me that juice!

1:19:10.916 --> 1:19:14.666
For America! Charge!

1:19:15.375 --> 1:19:17.666
[Benedict] Artillery.
Open fire on the front.

1:19:17.750 --> 1:19:20.000
[soldier over speaker] But, my lord,
we'll hit our own men.

1:19:20.083 --> 1:19:21.750
Fuck's sake. I'm evil!

1:19:21.833 --> 1:19:24.541
We're the bad guys! Jesus, pay attention!

1:19:24.625 --> 1:19:28.375
Now, open fire or I'll eat your bones!

1:19:28.916 --> 1:19:30.166
[clears throat] Commander.

1:19:30.250 --> 1:19:34.000
[commander over speaker] Roger, roger.
All cannon, open fire. Danger close.

1:19:49.291 --> 1:19:51.458
We've gotta do something
about those cannons!

1:19:52.166 --> 1:19:53.875
Wait a minute. Is that Martha?

1:19:54.625 --> 1:19:57.041
Oh, my God! Edison, on me!

1:20:01.708 --> 1:20:04.041
[grunts] Paul, take out those walkers
or we're sunk!

1:20:04.125 --> 1:20:06.666
-Affirmative. Commencing attack run.
-Edison, give me a lift.

1:20:06.750 --> 1:20:09.291
I'm on it! Science, don't fail me now.

1:20:12.083 --> 1:20:15.250
-[George] Edison, fly straight!
-[Edison] My thrusters took some damage!

1:20:15.333 --> 1:20:17.500
Just get me to that elephant!

1:20:17.583 --> 1:20:19.041
-[grunting]
-[screaming]

1:20:23.958 --> 1:20:27.666
-[Martha in British accent] Ello, guv'ner!
-[laughing] Oh, Martha! Thank God!

1:20:27.750 --> 1:20:30.625
I'm just so happy that you're… safe?

1:20:35.041 --> 1:20:36.250
Stay on target.

1:20:38.125 --> 1:20:40.291
Stay on target.

1:20:49.125 --> 1:20:50.375
[bellows]

1:20:50.458 --> 1:20:54.041
Well, Manchester,
if you want something done right…

1:20:55.333 --> 1:20:56.625
[growls]

1:20:56.708 --> 1:20:59.666
Get some! Get some! Get some! [grunts]

1:21:01.458 --> 1:21:03.416
-What the… What are you?
-[snaps]

1:21:03.500 --> 1:21:05.166
[bellows]

1:21:11.666 --> 1:21:13.250
[screaming]

1:21:18.375 --> 1:21:20.916
Oi! Handball! That's a foul, ya wanker!

1:21:21.000 --> 1:21:22.833
Maybe that's true in Britain.

1:21:24.666 --> 1:21:27.250
But this is America, asshole! [grunts]

1:21:27.333 --> 1:21:28.500
[screams]

1:21:29.250 --> 1:21:30.666
Touchdown!

1:21:30.750 --> 1:21:33.333
[Benedict] What is the deal
with these chaps?

1:21:33.416 --> 1:21:35.458
It's like they have no quit in them.

1:21:35.541 --> 1:21:39.208
No matter,
I guess I'll just skip to the end, then.

1:21:39.291 --> 1:21:41.916
Game over, old friend.

1:21:45.625 --> 1:21:47.625
[machinery whirring]

1:21:59.750 --> 1:22:02.208
We're surrounded.
Why aren't they advancing?

1:22:02.291 --> 1:22:05.541
Because that's not part
of the plan, ya dumb twat!

1:22:05.625 --> 1:22:07.875
Oh, fuck!

1:22:12.291 --> 1:22:14.625
Holy! What is that thing?

1:22:14.708 --> 1:22:17.375
It's a weather control device.
Look at the tea bags.

1:22:17.458 --> 1:22:20.791
It's designed to seed the clouds…
with tea!

1:22:20.875 --> 1:22:23.541
Teabagging them? Literally? But why?

1:22:23.625 --> 1:22:26.083
To make them rain tea.

1:22:26.166 --> 1:22:29.208
Every man, woman and child
beneath these spacious skies

1:22:29.291 --> 1:22:31.250
will be turned British instantly.

1:22:31.333 --> 1:22:33.083
The revolution will not only be over,

1:22:33.166 --> 1:22:35.250
it will effectively
have never even occurred.

1:22:35.333 --> 1:22:38.666
Aw, fuck! These are those global stakes
you were talking about, aren't they?

1:22:38.750 --> 1:22:42.916
Yep. If he successfully British-izes
every colonist in the New World,

1:22:43.000 --> 1:22:46.666
he won't stop there.
He'll British-ize the entire world.

1:22:46.750 --> 1:22:49.291
[chuckling] Okay. You know what? Fuck it.

1:22:50.041 --> 1:22:53.416
-It was fun while it lasted, boys.
-Keep it.

1:22:53.500 --> 1:22:56.958
This is your last moment as a colonist.
You may as well enjoy it.

1:22:57.041 --> 1:22:58.875
Besides, it's sorta perfect.

1:22:58.958 --> 1:23:01.041
I mean, beer's the exact opposite of tea.

1:23:01.125 --> 1:23:03.750
So, one last "fuck you"
to the Brits. Am I right?

1:23:04.625 --> 1:23:08.250
The exact opposite. That's it!
Sam, hold this keg steady.

1:23:08.333 --> 1:23:10.208
-But it's full of beer!
-It better be.

1:23:10.291 --> 1:23:12.791
-Blacksmith, hammer this valve into place.
-On it!

1:23:12.875 --> 1:23:15.000
Geronimo, keep track
of where that thing is headed.

1:23:15.083 --> 1:23:16.458
That won't be too hard.

1:23:20.666 --> 1:23:23.458
And, Paul, I'm gonna need a lot of juice!

1:23:23.541 --> 1:23:24.916
[engine revving]

1:23:27.500 --> 1:23:30.291
-Yo, Edison! What is that shit?
-It is science.

1:23:30.375 --> 1:23:32.625
The science that's going to win this war.

1:23:32.708 --> 1:23:35.166
Last time you tried "science,"

1:23:35.250 --> 1:23:37.708
you set off a bomb that almost killed us.

1:23:37.791 --> 1:23:39.708
How can you be so sure
that this will work?

1:23:39.791 --> 1:23:43.333
Well, I'm not sure, Sammy,
but I have a hypothesis.

1:23:43.916 --> 1:23:48.083
So, let's go test that hypothesis
and draw some fucking conclusions!

1:23:48.750 --> 1:23:53.583
This is for science!

1:23:53.666 --> 1:23:55.208
[echoing]

1:24:04.208 --> 1:24:05.875
[screams]

1:24:11.083 --> 1:24:12.666
[screaming]

1:24:15.708 --> 1:24:16.791
[grunts]

1:24:20.000 --> 1:24:24.500
No! No! Not like this!
Not like this, Martha!

1:24:24.583 --> 1:24:28.375
-Drink it, George! Drink it in.
-No! I won't do it! Ah!

1:24:28.458 --> 1:24:34.250
Fine, resist. And I'll gain full custody
of our son the moment he is born.

1:24:34.333 --> 1:24:36.750
And you'll be helpless to stop it.

1:24:36.833 --> 1:24:42.375
You'll have failed as a leader,
as a husband and as a father,

1:24:42.458 --> 1:24:46.833
just like your father before you.

1:24:46.916 --> 1:24:48.833
[laughs maniacally]

1:24:48.916 --> 1:24:51.208
Hey, hey, it's okay.

1:24:51.291 --> 1:24:53.541
Even though you totally blew it

1:24:53.625 --> 1:24:58.291
and let everyone on the team down,
you tried your best, witch.

1:24:58.375 --> 1:25:01.750
I'm not a witch, Sam. I am a scientist.

1:25:01.833 --> 1:25:03.625
And no, I did not.

1:25:03.708 --> 1:25:07.791
The beam. It wasn't meant to blow
the Teabagger out of the sky.

1:25:07.875 --> 1:25:09.333
-Nope.
-Horse sound.

1:25:09.416 --> 1:25:11.250
What did you do, human lady friend?

1:25:11.333 --> 1:25:13.791
I reversed the polarity of the tea.

1:25:22.083 --> 1:25:24.833
So, if it ain't tea no more,
what the fuck is it?

1:25:24.916 --> 1:25:26.750
The exact opposite of tea.

1:25:28.458 --> 1:25:31.916
[gasps] It's beer! Beer won the war!

1:25:32.000 --> 1:25:34.500
What? No, beer didn't win… No, science!

1:25:34.583 --> 1:25:36.375
[all] Bro!

1:25:38.125 --> 1:25:42.166
I'd just like to say something,
you know, as the leader of the group.

1:25:42.250 --> 1:25:45.500
Thirty minutes ago,
I dreamed of a bigger fraternity.

1:25:45.583 --> 1:25:49.375
And now, I look around and I have it.

1:25:50.166 --> 1:25:52.625
That's the power
of positive thinking, guys.

1:25:52.708 --> 1:25:55.583
-Believe in yourselves!
-Are you kidding me?

1:25:55.666 --> 1:25:57.916
Mmm, delicious, isn't it?

1:25:58.000 --> 1:25:59.708
[coughs]

1:26:10.416 --> 1:26:11.416
[eagle screeches]

1:26:17.791 --> 1:26:19.041
Ah!

1:26:21.708 --> 1:26:24.500
Oh! George? What happened?

1:26:24.583 --> 1:26:27.333
Science, Martha. Science happened.

1:26:27.416 --> 1:26:29.708
Oh, my God! I could have… I almost…

1:26:29.791 --> 1:26:32.666
[shushes] No, don't you worry about that.

1:26:32.750 --> 1:26:36.833
You're back now
and we've just got one thing left to do.

1:26:36.916 --> 1:26:38.750
-Have awesome sex!
-Final boss battle. What?

1:26:38.833 --> 1:26:41.250
Uh, yep. Yep. Final boss battle.

1:26:41.333 --> 1:26:42.750
-Bro!
-No!

1:26:42.833 --> 1:26:45.666
Bros. Bros everywhere!

1:26:45.750 --> 1:26:48.750
It reeks of Ye Olde Axe body spray!

1:26:48.833 --> 1:26:50.083
[George] Excuse me, sir.

1:26:53.750 --> 1:26:56.083
Do you have a moment
to talk about freedom?

1:26:56.166 --> 1:27:00.750
Aren't you surprised to see me
leading the British and not King James?

1:27:00.833 --> 1:27:03.583
What? No. You obviously
pulled a Benedict Arnold.

1:27:03.666 --> 1:27:04.666
A what?

1:27:04.750 --> 1:27:07.041
A Benedict Arnold.
You're a thing now, bro.

1:27:07.125 --> 1:27:09.666
Whenever you get fucked over
by a trusted friend,

1:27:09.750 --> 1:27:12.333
it's called getting Benedict Arnolded.
Right, everybody?

1:27:12.416 --> 1:27:14.458
-[all] Yeah.
-It's totally a thing.

1:27:14.541 --> 1:27:16.791
No. You… You can't just do that.

1:27:16.875 --> 1:27:19.875
Oh, yeah, we can.
Because we all voted on it.

1:27:19.958 --> 1:27:21.333
And that's called…

1:27:21.416 --> 1:27:23.125
[all] Fucking Democracy!

1:27:23.208 --> 1:27:24.416
We're doin' it!

1:27:24.500 --> 1:27:26.833
[laughing] Oh, Georgie.

1:27:26.916 --> 1:27:29.000
You think you've won.

1:27:30.416 --> 1:27:31.833
[growls]

1:27:32.416 --> 1:27:35.041
Mega Wolf!

1:27:35.125 --> 1:27:36.000
Geronimo, now!

1:27:37.458 --> 1:27:38.500
Launch winch-chain.

1:27:39.208 --> 1:27:41.125
-[grunts]
-[neighs]

1:27:41.208 --> 1:27:42.541
[growls]

1:27:43.208 --> 1:27:44.583
Sammy, take the shot!

1:27:45.541 --> 1:27:47.500
Here comes the boom, bitch.

1:27:48.791 --> 1:27:50.333
[grunting]

1:27:52.791 --> 1:27:55.416
[growling]

1:27:58.416 --> 1:27:59.541
[grunts]

1:28:03.166 --> 1:28:05.333
Guys, I don't know
how much more he can take!

1:28:05.416 --> 1:28:07.458
-Where's the stupid bullet?
-We're looking!

1:28:07.541 --> 1:28:10.458
Any last regrets, old chum?

1:28:10.541 --> 1:28:15.208
Yeah, I only regret that I have
but one life to give for my country.

1:28:15.291 --> 1:28:20.208
Yes. Well, I suppose
the one will have to do.

1:28:20.291 --> 1:28:23.416
Oh, shit! It's right here.
Guys! I found it!

1:28:24.541 --> 1:28:27.625
What are you smiling about, you idiot?
You can't possibly kill me.

1:28:27.708 --> 1:28:29.791
I'm not trying to kill you, Ben.

1:28:29.875 --> 1:28:34.083
They are. With America's favorite pastime.

1:28:34.166 --> 1:28:35.083
No!

1:28:39.791 --> 1:28:41.166
Tax this, motherfucker!

1:28:46.500 --> 1:28:48.583
[commentator]
It's going way back to right field.

1:28:48.666 --> 1:28:50.916
The bullet is still going!
High up in there!

1:28:51.000 --> 1:28:53.041
-Bugger!
-He did it!

1:28:53.833 --> 1:28:56.166
John Henry Smith did it!

1:28:56.250 --> 1:28:57.458
[all cheer]

1:29:01.583 --> 1:29:05.875
Welcome to America!

1:29:11.041 --> 1:29:12.875
[cheering]

1:29:16.833 --> 1:29:18.625
[whooping]

1:29:36.208 --> 1:29:38.125
[George] I wanna make a monument
for Abe, too.

1:29:38.208 --> 1:29:40.583
But of course, Mr. President.
Same as yours?

1:29:40.666 --> 1:29:41.750
No, I.M. Pei.

1:29:41.833 --> 1:29:47.500
His should be a statue of him
sitting there, staring at my monument.

1:29:47.583 --> 1:29:49.500
[Abe chuckling] Who are you, Demi Moore?

1:29:49.583 --> 1:29:51.625
Why you gotta screw
a ghost like that, George?

1:29:51.708 --> 1:29:54.916
Abe! Ah, bro!
God, it's good to see you again, man.

1:29:55.000 --> 1:29:58.958
Well, you're gonna feel like a real turd
after you see what I brought you. Hah!

1:29:59.041 --> 1:30:00.916
The Declaration! You saved it!

1:30:01.000 --> 1:30:01.916
I did.

1:30:02.000 --> 1:30:05.041
A little of Mr. Scotch's invisible tape
and it's as good as new.

1:30:05.125 --> 1:30:06.166
It's beautiful, Abe.

1:30:06.250 --> 1:30:09.916
It is, but you're the real
national treasure here, George.

1:30:10.000 --> 1:30:11.458
I'm proud of you, bud.

1:30:13.541 --> 1:30:16.708
And no, there's no treasure map
drawn on the back of it.

1:30:16.791 --> 1:30:18.833
-Oh, man.
-George, what are you doin', bro?

1:30:18.916 --> 1:30:20.708
-They're lookin' for you out there.
-Oh, Sam!

1:30:20.791 --> 1:30:23.125
I'm glad you're here.
I have something for you.

1:30:23.208 --> 1:30:26.375
-What is it?
-A gift for my son's godfather.

1:30:26.458 --> 1:30:27.708
-Who, me?
-Yep.

1:30:27.791 --> 1:30:31.083
I need someone
I can trust with my son's life.

1:30:31.166 --> 1:30:33.250
And I always thought it would be Abe.

1:30:33.333 --> 1:30:37.041
But with him as a gho… a goner,
I need to find someone else.

1:30:37.125 --> 1:30:39.166
George, I'm honored!

1:30:39.250 --> 1:30:40.666
Hey, is that my hat? Oh, it is.

1:30:40.750 --> 1:30:43.916
But… Ugh. I don't know
how to be a caretaker.

1:30:44.000 --> 1:30:45.458
I don't have those instincts.

1:30:45.541 --> 1:30:47.916
No, don't think of it
as being the caretaker.

1:30:48.000 --> 1:30:49.333
Think of it as being family.

1:30:49.416 --> 1:30:50.750
Like the fun, drunk,

1:30:50.833 --> 1:30:55.833
now definitely no-longer-racist uncle
that America has always needed.

1:30:55.916 --> 1:30:58.875
Uncle Sam. I like It.

1:30:58.958 --> 1:31:00.875
Uncle fucking Sam!

1:31:00.958 --> 1:31:04.250
Come on, Uncle Sam, our countrymen await.

1:31:05.916 --> 1:31:08.666
[crowd cheering and applauding]

1:31:14.625 --> 1:31:15.708
Hey, Denzel.

1:31:15.791 --> 1:31:16.708
[giggles]

1:31:18.083 --> 1:31:19.583
[crowd cheers]

1:31:26.458 --> 1:31:28.000
My fellow Americans,

1:31:28.083 --> 1:31:32.750
on this day, July 4th, 1776,

1:31:32.833 --> 1:31:36.916
we are all finally free!

1:31:37.000 --> 1:31:38.958
[all cheer]

1:31:48.000 --> 1:31:49.666
[man 1] What about your slaves?

1:31:49.750 --> 1:31:52.416
Oh! Um…

1:31:52.500 --> 1:31:56.916
-I said, what about your slaves?
-[George] Well, see--

1:31:57.000 --> 1:31:58.375
And what about women?

1:31:58.458 --> 1:32:01.291
Will we be granted equality
in your America?

1:32:01.375 --> 1:32:04.250
-Yes, but--
-Sure, right after the Indians.

1:32:04.333 --> 1:32:07.750
Wait a second. I was under the impression
we were getting our land back.

1:32:07.833 --> 1:32:08.833
Good point. Um…

1:32:08.916 --> 1:32:10.791
Oh, hey, can I keep this here machine gun?

1:32:10.875 --> 1:32:13.541
Like, if a Mexican
tries to take my property or something?

1:32:13.625 --> 1:32:15.833
What? You just took this land
from the Indians--

1:32:15.916 --> 1:32:17.583
He was coming for you. I saw it!

1:32:17.666 --> 1:32:20.958
-He just shot him! In the back!
-He was making a move, man. I swear it!

1:32:21.041 --> 1:32:24.583
We're gonna have a fair
and unbiased judicial process, right?

1:32:24.666 --> 1:32:27.041
-Everyone, just calm down!
-Fuck you!

1:32:27.125 --> 1:32:28.541
No, fuck you!

1:32:28.625 --> 1:32:30.791
Hey, I just wanna marry my boyfriend.

1:32:31.458 --> 1:32:32.500
Sinner!

1:32:32.583 --> 1:32:34.875
There's gonna be
comprehensive health care, right?

1:32:36.083 --> 1:32:38.958
[man 1] Seriously, dude.
What about your slaves?

1:32:39.041 --> 1:32:42.541
Oh, God.
We're gonna fuck this up, aren't we?

1:33:35.541 --> 1:33:38.291
Dagnabbit! I think we missed it, E's.

1:33:38.375 --> 1:33:40.083
[growls weakly]
